summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2014 DODGE DURANGO. WHILE DRIVING 35 MPH, THE CHECK ENGINE WARNING AND SHIFT TO PARK WARNING INDICATORS ILLUMINATED. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE VEHICLE SLOWED INDEPENDENTLY AND STALLED. THERE WAS ALSO AN ABNORMAL FUEL ODOR PRESENT. THE CONTACT WAS ABLE TO RESTART THE VEHICLE AFTER PARKING THE VEHICLE FOR TEN MINUTES. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT DIAGNOSED OR REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE APPROXIMATE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 61,000.
